76561197972610454,Recommended,303590,14078172,"Posted: 19 January, 2015",all,Mose Schrute,"Short version:  Buy this game if you have a) Multiple 360-compatible controllers in your home and b) people that want to play while sitting next to you.  You will not regret it.  If you don't have those requirements then there is no reason to buy this game.Long version:This game is a riot that's really easy to recommend to the right audience.  If you like playing games couch co-op with your kids or having people over for party games, it's WELL worth the $5.  Imagine being a character in a where's waldo picture, only all the other characters are moving around, and you have to assassinate as many of them as you can before snipers discover and kill you.  That's the general concept behind this game.There are several game modes with different objectives and teams.  Some are more fun than others - death race looks the lamest but turned out to be the most fun for my group.  I played this game with three of my kids ages 10, 8, and 7 and they loved it.This game could be a LOT better with more game modes or more polished gameplay.  It's not always clear who ""won"" in a particular round, for example.  But that didn't stop me and the family from enjoying the crap out of it."
