76561197991681312,Recommended,303590,25626770,"Posted: 21 September, 2016",all,Zantis,"Must-Have for every Couchlover. Though half of the modes are barely any fun, the other 3 make up a very fun experience.You should play this game with some house rules, since the built-in systems do not support some mandatory stuff.I recommend the game for the following:Death Race: Extremely fun. Everyone is one of the about 20 characters on screen, the other being NPCs. You can only Press A to walk or Y to run and shoot with a crosshair on screen. First to finish wins, but if you are too obvious someone will shoot you and you are out.Houserule: sadly, the game does not give you the ability to get an extra shot if you actually killed one of your friends. So just set shots to 4, only have everybody shooting once, except they get a player kill, which gives them another one. WAY better that way.Thief Party: Fun overall. There are 2 Teams, thiefs and snipers. the thieves are one of the otherwise NPC characters on the field, about 20. There are coins, which give a sound once a thief walks over it and they disappear a random time after that. Snipers have a crosshair and 3 shots to kill the thieves. You should always play 2 rounds, switching teams on each. The thieves which collect more coins win. If the snipers waste all their shots, the thieves win automatically and a new set of round starts.Assassins: Same as thief Party basically, but the assassins kill the NPCs instead of collecting coins. Same fun though and still quite different to play out.The other gamemodes are quite awful though.Nonetheless: MUST-HAVE. Extremely fun to play. Even if you are only playing this for 20 mins on a day with your friends on your couch, it is totally worth it every time."
